Day 3

	Create a new rails app

	  $ rails new (PROJECT NAME)
	  $ rails new pinteresting 

	Run rails server from within project, so it knows which application to run that server for.

		$ cd pinteresting
	  $ rails server 
	  $ rails s
	  $ ctrl + c

Day 4

	Setup git 

	  $ git config --global user.name "MY NAME"
	  $ git config --global user.email "MY EMAIL"

	  To check:

	    $ git config --global user.name
	    $ git config --global user.email

	Initialize git in project

	  $ git init
	  $ git status

	Get rid of .DS_STORE .gitignore file

	  I guess rails automatically doesn't have .DS_STORE

	Commit changes

	  $ git add .
	  $ git commit -am "Create initial repo"

	  -a flag helps keep track of deleted files

	Go back to last version:

    $ git checkout -f

Day 5

  Use SSH to connect to github account from local.

  Create a new key

    $ ssh-keygen -t rsa -C "MY EMAIL"
    Enter passphrase

  Now we have a key, let's add that key to github

    google: github ssh keys & Follow instructions

  Once all setup, create a new repo for your project

  ALREADY SET UP SSH ONCE, NEVER AGAIN.

  $ git remote add origin https://github.com/alealejandro/pinteresting2.git

  $ git push origin master

  https://stackoverflow.com/questions/10904339/github-fatal-remote-origin-already-exists

